-- Iran Arrests 20 Suspects in Atomic Scientist Killings, IRNA Says
-- B y   Y e g a n e h   S a l e h i
-- 2012-06-17T12:48:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-17/iran-arrests-20-suspects-in-atomic-scientist-killings-irna-says.html
Iran has arrested 20 people
suspected of involvement in the assassinations of its nuclear
scientists, the official  Islamic Republic News Agency  reported,
citing Intelligence Minister Heidar Moslehi.  Moslehi said ministry agents made the arrests after busting
two groups linked to Israel. He said the ministry wasn’t
releasing information such as the location of the arrests for
“technical reasons.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yeganeh Salehi in Dubai at 
 yalehi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
